optional_parameters.description:
If your subscription is not BASIC, you can put a custom alias to your shorten link. Due to the philosophy of this project, it can only take 15 characters. If you put an alias like \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"test\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", your shortened link will look like this: 2d.al/test.

If your URL is already saved with a different alias and if you are the owner of shortened URL, It can be overridden. If you are not of short link, the API will return with {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"permission\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"You can only override your short urls\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}

If your subscription is BASIC, the API will return 400 with {auth: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"subscription level is not sufficient\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}

api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://url-shortener-tiny-url-qr-builder-www-2d-al.p.rapidapi.com/api/create"
querystring = {"alias": "", "url": ""}

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "url-shortener-tiny-url-qr-builder-www-2d-al.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, params=querystring)
print(response.json())

